1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Imagine a teaspoon of matter weighing billions of tons.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,000
That’s the reality of neutron stars, the remnants of supernova explosions.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:14,800
These stellar corpses pack more mass than our Sun into a sphere the size of a city.

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:19,200
One teaspoon of neutron star material could crush anything on Earth.

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,400
Their intense gravity creates bizarre phenomena, like pulsars—rotating stars emitting beams of radiation.

6
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Curious about more cosmic wonders?

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:29,200
Hit follow for the latest in astrophysics!
